 <H1>Conceptual Design Using the ER Model</H1> 
 <P><UL>
<LI><H2>Design choices:
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>Should a concept be modelled as an entity or an attribute?
<LI>Should a concept be modelled as an entity or a relationship?
<LI>Identifying relationships: Binary or ternary? Aggregation?
</UL></UL><UL>
<LI><H2>Constraints in the ER Model:
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>A lot of data semantics can (and should) be captured.
<LI>But some constraints cannot be captured in ER diagrams.
</UL></UL><UL>
<LI><H2>Need for further refining the schema:
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>Relational schema obtained from ER diagram is a good first step.  But ER design subjective & can’t express certain constraints; so this relational schema may need refinement.</UL></UL></P>
